// Polymorphism
// It means one name but many forms
// same functions behaving differently depending on the type of objectif called
//Two Types
// Compile time Polymorphism -- function overloading -- Static
// Resolve at compile time
// function overloads -- same function name , but different parameters
// faster execution
// Run time Polymorphism -- function overriding -- Dynamic
// resolved at run time
// function runtime -- same function name,same parameters,but different class
// uses a virtual keyword in the base class
// achieving this through the concept of Inheritance

